  <cateringDescription><![CDATA[<p>A delicious buffet breakfast is served daily offering a range of hot and cold items from 7.30am to 10.30am. If you book half board, evening meals can be taken at the <strong>Atlântida</strong> restaurant from 6.30pm to 9.30pm. The Atlântida restaurant serves a buffet with international cuisine and overlooks the pool and gardens. Every evening there is a different theme with show cooking. </p>
<p>Part of the Vila Porto Mare resort, guests at the Hotel Porto Mare have access to all of the resort's facilities. If you don't want to venture too far in the evenings you can enjoy one of the hotels à la carte restaurants. <strong>Alfama</strong> offers a taste of Portuguese and Madeiran cuisine, <strong>Il Basilico Madeira</strong> is an Italian-inspired restaurant that's popular with the locals too, and <strong>Horta</strong> is open from Wednesday until Sunday and has an innovative menu that introduces the concept of healthy comfort food (these restaurants can be booked and paid locally).</p>
<p>The poolside <strong>Varanda</strong> bar offers lighter, more informal meals throughout the day, and <strong>Portofino Bar</strong> has a Happy Hour from 5-6 pm every evening.</p>
<p>In the evening we recommend heading to <strong>Oceano</strong> bar to enjoy the live music, or to watch your favourite football team.</p>
<ul>
<li>Guests on any board basis but staying on the 24th Dec 2024 and/or 31st Dec 2024 can enjoy a fantastic Christmas and/or New Years Eve Gala Dinner - these are included in the price of your holiday.</li>
</ul>]]></cateringDescription>
