  <description><![CDATA[<p>The Hotel Porto Mare is only a short journey from Funchal but feels like a sanctuary set in 13,000m² of tropical gardens. Expect great views, delicious food and an array of facilities to choose from.</p>
<h2>Tuck into delicious food</h2>
<p>We’re sure you’ll love the food at the Porto Mare with a number of bars and restaurants to choose from. Whether you’re in the mood for Italian or fancy some traditional Portuguese cuisine, the Hotel Porto Mare has a great selection. We love to head to the Oceano Bar in the evening and enjoy the live music whilst sipping on an aperitif. For guests staying on half board you can enjoy a delicious buffet dinner at the Atlântida restaurant.</p>
<h2>Endless facilities to enjoy</h2>
<p>If you’re looking to lounge by the pool, stay active on holiday or relax in a wonderful wellness area then the Porto Mare has it all. There are a mix of indoor and outdoor pools but with five to choose from, you’re sure to find one to suit you. The hotel is part of the Vila Porto Mare resort and benefits from all the resort's facilities. There’s a range of activities on offer at the hotel that are great for sports enthusiasts including tennis, fitness room and table tennis to name a few (some sports activities payable locally). The spa is always a hit with a great range of treatments and massages on offer (bookable and payable locally).</p>
<h2>Family-friendly resort</h2>
<p>The resort is great for those travelling with kids with a range of facilities and activities on offer. The children’s pool is always a hit and the mini-golf can be enjoyed by all the family and so can the on-site ice-cream parlour.</p>]]></description>
